reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent eyebrow kit
reviews.reviewText: I have tried many eyebrow products. I am looking for a product the creates a natural looking brow. I’ve tried traditional pencils, stamps, eyeshadows and gel pencils. Until I found this product my go to was Too Faced pomade In a pencil (picture to the left)., but that was starting to give a crusty texture. So when I saw this product I wanted to give it a shot. So glad I did. I’m a red head and the caramel matched perfectly (pictured right). It goes on with ease and washes off the same. My one complaint is that instead of giving a black eyeliner that they offer the eyeliner in the same color as the pomade.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I've been living in Eyebrow Hell for several years. Yep, so is girls who were teenagers in the 70s all over-plucked oureyebrows..oh excuse me...I was told by my hairdresser to call it Tweezing. She says, " You pluck a chicken, you tweeze your brows😂 Fast forward 30-40 years and we barely have anything left to tweeze! I have the front parts left... the lil patch of hair closest to our nose... and that is getting thinner with age. I've been drawing on my eyebrows for years with just drug store pencils. Well. I want more. I checked into Micro- blading. $650😳 Then I tried these little tiny jars the size of quarters, "gel". It was great at first but the stuff dries out and it becomes thick and hard to use. Then those amazing Stamps were invented. I got some. The lightest color they had was "Med. Brown". Holding the stencil where your eyebrows are is really hard using 2 fingers. I placed the stencil and Stamped and...OMG!! I looked likeGroucho Marx! It was BLACK and the stencil was HUGE!! It came with 6 stencils and they all looked the same. Anyway.. then I found some Eyebrow Tattoo stuff you are supposed to paint on, wait 2-6 hours then "peel" off the..stuff.. and baby let me tell you what. I need to start reading reviews. If I had I would have NEVER gotten these things. There was NO PEELING! There was ripping, tearing, crying, swearing and just the worst stuff ever. What few brow hairs i DID have were torn off my face with that crap. And there was NO TATTOO! I Looked Like a Drag Queen Before she paints her face (In in love with RuePaul's Dragrace so I know a thing or two about Drag Queens and i Love them all. Ok so.. now I have 4 hairs left to work with on each brow and I found LAVONE. Oh my Stars!! This is what I've been looking for, for years! It's really great stuff!! I basically paint on my brows. I use eyeshadow primer first then I paint them on and they will last a day or two at least. I've gone longer but with touch ups. They have a great color selection. I use "Warm Brown". I also ordered "Taupe " just to be sure i had the right color. I'm not Taupe, Warm Brown is perfect. It comes with a tiny brow brush, (I use my own) and a beautiful eyeliner...I have up trying to do that years ago. It also comes with a twist up classic brow pencil with a lil Spoolie at the other end. This is called Pomade. Its so smooth and creamy. Very easy to apply. When it dries it STAYS ON ALL DAY and the next day! ...As long as you use primer. It's not coming off unless you want it off. I've used coconut oil for EVERYTHING!! Makeup remover moisturizer, suntan oil, leather conditioner. Dental Pulling (Google that girls.. once you start you'll never stop. It's VERY GOOD for your dental hygiene )Well that's all. I hope you buy and try this kit. It's the answer to my prayers!! I'm not ever going to stop buying this. It's price is VERY REASONABLE!! What's $15 when it comes to looking fabulous at any age. I'm 65 and I'm always having to pull out my I.D. to prove my age to someone. It's the best compliment I get! Enjoy!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Easy to use, I dont really wear make up and use this to fill in my gaps. Blends in very well. I would say if I used a setting spray it might be smudge proof but it will definitely move if you wipe your eyebrow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I was a certified eyeshadow for everything makeup girly. I thought it was time to get actual brow products & I'm glad I tried this. The reviews looked great & I scrolled for a while to decide. I tested everything on my hand and the eyeliner was on point, the pomade consistency was great and buildable w the pressure of the brush. The pencil was also great, doesn't break easily, has a eyeliner stamp looking shape for several techniques with different angles. Great kit to create the perfect brow

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Very hard to remove!!
reviews.reviewText: I liked the angled brush, I like the pomade, but I found it VERY hard to get it off. I even used “Take off’s” which are normally a very good make-up remover. But I felt like I had to rub my eye lash area TOO hard to get the pomade off. Even the next day, I still saw some on my eyelids.The liquid liner is very nice, but I’m not good at using it yet. The pencil part was nice for my eyebrows, but I wish it had a much smaller angled brush on the opposite end, instead of just the one big side.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So glad I got this!
reviews.reviewText: I used my old eyebrow stuff for a long time and was wanting to try something new but like the pomade so I was looking for that. This brush and formula is literally so soft it just glides on! I love it! I have not used the pencil or the eyeliner but I am sure they are wonderful too. Not bad for a great deal!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This one is the right color
reviews.reviewText: I purchased one like this in a different color going by the colors online. Well it was too dark. I emailed them and only got a message that said *I should try a lighter color. No offer of a return or any money back. I went ahead and ordered a different and this one worked Still not happy about no offer of help when I emailed them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Does the job but not the best
reviews.reviewText: Really wanted to love this kit - it's very easy to use and the pomade works well but the brow pencil does not last long, smudges easily and goes on rather thick. It's very hard to define your brows with it as well. The pomade and brush are great and easy to control without smudging but the pencil needs work. It would be good for a very light fill in but nothing too detailed
